Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Heat a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}.

Fry until the mince has browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the pork cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2%cloves}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and halve the @Green Beans{80%grams}.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the garlic to the pork and stir-fry, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Soy Sauce{15%milliliters}, @Gochujang Paste{50%grams}, @Sugar{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliters} into the pan and stir to combine.

Bring the sauce up to the boil, add the green beans, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with some #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the mince is tender and the sauce has thickened, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Rice ==

While the pork cooks, pour the @Water for the Rice{300%milliliters} into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Finishing ==

When everything's ready, remove the pork from the oven and stir through the @BBQ Sauce{32%grams}. Taste and season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your bowls.

Top with your BBQ pork mince and sprinkle over the @Roasted White Sesame Seeds{5%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!